cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the prediction of human mobility using machine learning methods and information-theoretic concepts. It also focuses on the impact of device types on predictability. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
